The South African Weather Service says another cold front is expected to hit the Cape later this week. This as most of the country is currently experiencing icy cold weather conditions. Forecaster, Henning Grobbler says colder conditions will set in on Wednesday. This as most of the country is currently experiencing icy cold weather conditions. Grobbler says this cold front will not bring much rain. “There’s another cold front set in over Cape Town by very late Wednesday evening into Thursday morning and that cold front should be here for the whole day of Thursday right into Friday morning with some rain and showers expected. It will start to clear up fairly quickly by Saturday during the course of the early morning, still some partly cloudy conditions clearing up quite nicely towards Sunday. This cold front is just a weak cold front brushing through, don’t expect a lot of rain out of it about ten to 15 millimeters.” Watch related videos:  